I've been living in Tampa for less than a year (came from Miami) and haven't found a great  restaurant that serves authentic Cuban food UNTIL NOW. I gotta say for a tiny little "food truck" it really has the best food I've tasted since Miami. The Media noches were amazing! The rice, red beans and lechon were so flavorful and delicious and even the ham croquettes were to die for! Not to mention the owner was really nice and friendly. My husband is Cuban and he loved all the food (said it was legit lol) I definitely recommend La Cocinita Cubana and I'll be returning to try the other menu items. 👍😋

This place has been around for almost 5 years and I never knew about it.  How does that even happen?  When we moved to Brandon we tried to find Cuban coffee as good as La Terecita with no luck.  We just found it.  If you want La Teresita coffee without the drive come here.  We also tried the Cuban sandwich and WOW it was excellent. She said she makes her own Mojo and it's tangy and delicious. Do yourselves a favor and try this food.  If you don't love this place then you don't like Cuban food.
